    <h1>Chess Openings</h1>

<p>
Chess openings are the first phase of the game.
They focus on controlling the center, developing pieces,
and preparing for the middle game.
</p>

<h2>Italian Game</h2>
    <img src="../images/italian-game.png" width="300" alt="Italian Game opening" />
<p>
The Italian Game is one of the oldest chess openings.
It focuses on quick development and control of the center.
</p>
    <p>
        more info about the Italian Game in: 
        <a href="https://www.chess.com/openings/Italian-Game" 
           target="_blank" class="external-link">
            chess.com
        </a>
    </p>

<h2>Ruy López</h2>
    <img src="../Images/ruy-lopez.png" width="300" alt="Ruy Lopez opening" />
<p>
The Ruy López is a classical opening that puts pressure on Black’s knight
and aims for long-term positional play.
</p>
    <p>
        more info about the Ruy López opening in: 
        <a href="https://www.chess.com/openings/Ruy-Lopez-Opening" target="b" 
           class="external-link">
            chess.com
        </a>
    </p>




<h2>Sicilian Defense</h2>
    <img src="../images/sicilian-classical-variation.png" width="300" alt="Sicilian Defense opening" />
<p>
The Sicilian Defense is a popular aggressive response to 1.e4.
It leads to unbalanced positions and dynamic play.
</p>
    <p>
        more info about the Scilian Defence in:
        <a href="https://www.chess.com/openings/Sicilian-Defense" target="_blank"
           class="external-link">
            chess.com
        </a>
    </p>




<h2>Queen’s Gambit</h2>
    <img src="../images/queens-gambit.jpg" width="300" alt="Queen's Gambit opening" />
<p>
The Queen’s Gambit is a strategic opening where White offers a pawn
to gain strong control of the center.
</p>
    <p>
    If you would like to read more about the Queens Gambit and other variatons of it you can check out this link:
    </p>
    <a href="https://www.chess.com/openings/Queens-Gambit" target="_blank"
       class="external-link">
        Queens Gambit Opening & Variations
    </a>



